Several refugees have been arrested for occupying vacant land in District six. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - At least two refugees have been arrested in Cape Town during a standoff with police. The refugees are occupying a piece of land in the city after they were forcibly removed on Sunday from the Central Methodist church. READ: Trespassing case opened against Cape Town refugees However, the city obtained a court order that prevents them from occupying land anywhere in the CBD.